      "content": "Ah, the escrow account, a treasure chest guarded by the wise old goblin of trust, ensuring that both you and the seller of the house in Toronto are playing fair in the grand game of property exchange. You see, this magical goblin doesn't just keep your gold safe; it also makes sure that the seller doesn't pocket your hard-earned coins until every last one of the house's promises has been kept. It's like a pact between two goblins, where neither party can claim victory until the other has fulfilled their part of the bargain. So, without this trusty goblin, chaos would reign, and the house might as well be a dragon's hoard, guarded by a greedy goblin who won't let you near it until you've paid him a hefty tribute. But with the escrow account, you can rest easy knowing that your house and your gold are safe in the goblin's care until the closing day, when the goblin will finally release them, allowing you to claim your new home and treasure.",
